<HEADLINE> Sweden Takes 2-1 Lead Over Italy in Davis Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, September 19 (Xinhua) -- Sweden took a 2-1 lead over
Italy after winning the doubles in the second day of the Davis Cup
World Group semi-final in Norrkoeping of Sweden on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Nicklas Kulti and Jonas Bjorkman gave Sweden the victory by
tourncing Diego Nargiso and Omar Camporese of Italy 6-1, 6-1, 6-2.
</P>
<P>
Ealier on Friday, Jonas Bjorkman put Sweden to a 1-0 lead after
beating Omar Camporese of Italy 6-7 (5/7), 6-3, 6-2, 3-6, 6-3.
</P>
<P>
But Renzo Furlan of Italy levelled the scores at 1-all with
rallying win of 3-6, 6-3, 6-4, 3-6, 6-3 over Thomas Enqvist of
Sewden in the second singles. 
</P>
</TEXT>
