<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zimbabwean Govt Rapped for Declining Health </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, September 20 (Xinhua) -- The opposition Zimbabwe
People's Democratic Party today lashed out at the government's
"care-free attitude" toward the welfare of health personnel at a
time when the country's services are crumbling.
</P>
<P>
"This care-free attitude to matters only serves to prompt more
trained or qualified medical personnel to other countries in
search of employment from which they will get better
remuneration," said party leader Isabel Madangure.
</P>
<P>
Madangure said in a statement that the government should move
swiftly and arrest the loss of qualified personnel to other
countries by awarding attractive remunerations.
</P>
<P>
Health and Child Welfare Minister Timothy Stamps told
parliament recently that the government had since approved
establishment of a health review commission to probe the
country's ailing health delivery service.
</P>
<P>
The minister also bemoaned the loss of skilled personnel from
his ministry to the private sector and international
organizations, saying this was affecting "efficiency" at the top.
</P>
</TEXT>
