<HEADLINE> Bulgarian Press Reports on CPC Congress Conclusion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, September 20 (Xinhua) -- Bulgarian news media today
reported the conclusion of the 15th National Congress of the
Communist Party of China (CPC) with extensive coverage.
</P>
<P>
A lengthy report by a senior writer of the official Bulgarian
Telegraph Agency (BTA) hailed the CPC congress, which was ended in
Beijing on Friday, as an event of "very great significance."
</P>
<P>
The report, by Pavel Pachev, chief of the BTA's economic
information division and once a Beijing-based correspondent, was
carried by the Bulgarian daily Kontinent.
</P>
<P>
The CPC congress charted the way for the next five years, and
Jiang Zemin's re-election as the CPC Central Committee's general
secretary enabled him to focus on economic reforms, Pachev wrote.
</P>
<P>
In foreign relations, he said, Beijing has made it clear that
it will adhere to the principle of peaceful co-existence, expand
friendship with other countries and respect their sovereignty.
</P>
<P>
China, whose gross domestic product (GDP) is predicted to be
over that of the United States sometime between 2010 and 2020, has
also pledged not to seek hegemonism as its economy booms, he said.
</P>
<P>
To show its sincerity for peace, the CPC congress proposed
further reducing China's armed forces by 500,000, his report
added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
