<HEADLINE> Russian Press Comment on CPC's 15th National Congress </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 20 (Xinhua) -- Major Russian newspapers today
covered the 15th National Congress of the Communist Party of China
(CPC) and praised its resolution to further economic reforms.
</P>
<P>
The Russian Newspaper, the organ of the Russian government,
expressed the belief in an editorial that the new CPC leaders
elected at the Congress will guide China into the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
China's economic reform will focus on the public sector in next
five years, and the CPC leaders have formulated a careful policy
for political reform to avoid domestic turmoils, said the article.
</P>
<P>
"The establishment of socialist democracy is a historical
procedure that should be carried out step by step," it said.
</P>
<P>
China's planned disarmament of 500,000 troops in the next three
years, announced by CPC General Secretary Jiang Zemin, is a
positive move to make better use of national resources, it said.
</P>
<P>
Another popular Russian newspaper Izvestiya, or News, today
continued its coverage on the CPC congress in Beijing, hailing
that China "has embarked on the road to a new century."
</P>
<P>
"In the turn of the century, China is to undergo its most
fundamental changes after beginning the reform process 20 years
ago," the newspaper's correspondents reported from Beijing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
