Secretary-General of Namibia's ruling Southwest African People's
Organization (SWAPO) Moses Garoeb has died in Windhoek after a
long illness, President Sam Nujoma announced today.
</P>
<P>
Garoeb, 52, died at the Windhoek state hospital on Friday. He
had been suffering from diabetes and high blood pressure.
</P>
