Sunday. A state funeral, the first of its kind since Namibia's
independence in 1990, was being arranged, sources reaching here
said.
</P>
<P>
"It is with a deep sense of profound sorrow that i hereby
announce the untimely death of comrade Moses Garoeb," Nujoma
said.
</P>
<P>
Garoeb, who played a prominent role in the country's
liberation struggle and after independence died because of ill
health.
</P>
<P>
He is survived by his wife Monica, four sons and two
daughters. 
