<HEADLINE> IMF Reiterates Implementation of HIPC Initiative </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Hong Kong, September 21 (Xinhua) -- The International Monetary
Fund (IMF) today reaffirmed its determination to help the highly
indebted poor countries (HIPCs) by implementing an HIPC Initiative
 which aims to reduce the debt burden of those countries.
</P>
<P>
At a press conference following a one-day meeting of the IMF's
Interim Committee, committee chairman Philippe Maystadt urged
member countries to make contributions to the fund for the HIPC
Initiative.
</P>
<P>
"Further steps to secure the timely funding of these
initiatives would have to be considered soon," the Interim
Committee said in a communique.
</P>
<P>
The committee welcomed the recent progress made in the
implementation of the HIPC Initiative, including the decisions of
the Executive Boards of the IMF and the World Bank to provide
assistance to Uganda, Bolivia, and Burkina Faso, and their
preliminary discussions on Cote d'Ivoire, Guyana and Mozambique.
</P>
<P>
The countries that could qualify under the HIPC Initiative
should expeditiously take the necessary adjustment measures to
benefit from this special assistance, the committee said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
