<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sweden Beats Brazil in Davis Cup Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, Septebmer 21 (Xinhua) -- Sweden advanced into the
Davis Cup final in Norrkoeping, Sweden on Sunday after Jonas
Bjorkman defeated Renzo Furlan of Italy in the reverse singles.
</P>
<P>
The Swede roared back from one set down to beat the Italian
rival 4-6, 6-4, 6-0 and 6-4, which established an insurmountable
3-1 lead for home side.
</P>
<P>
The turning point came in the fifth set when Furlan served up a
string of double faults in the third to lose the set to love
before quickly finding himself 5-2 behind in the fourth. And
although he rallied to 5-4 he had left himself too much to do as
the 3,500 home crowd roared Bjorkman home.
</P>
<P>
Sweden will now face either the United States or Australia in
the final. The United States were leading 2-1 going into the final
day's play in Washington.
</P>
<P>
Thomas Enqvist was to face Omar Camporese in the final dead
rubber of Sweden's match later Sunday. 
