<HEADLINE> PLA Personnel Asked To Study CPC Congress Documents </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 21 (Xinhua) -- The General Political
Department of the People's Liberation Army (PLA) Saturday called
on PLA personnel and People's Armed Police (PAP) personnel to
conscientiously study the documents of the 15th National Congress
of the Communist Party of China.
</P>
<P>
In a circular distributed nationwide, the department said the
congress was a historic meeting held at a crucial time in the
country's reforms, opening up, and modernization drive, and was a
milestone in Party history.
</P>
<P>
Jiang Zemin's report to the congress, which was a historical
summary, outlines the plan for the future and makes a layout of the
country's development, and a political declaration and guiding
principle for the Party to lead the people into the new century,
the circular noted.
</P>
<P>
It said that designating the Deng Xiaoping Theory as the
Party's guiding ideology and its inclusion in the Party
Constitution by the congress is the will of the Party and the
aspiration of the people.
</P>
<P>
It emphasized that the new central leadership with Jiang Zemin
at the core will provide a strong organizational guarantee for
carrying China's cause from victory to victory.
</P>
<P>
The circular stressed that it is of paramount significance for
PLA and PAP personnel to conscientiously study the congress'
documents, because it will encourage them to hold the banner of
Deng Xiaoping Theory high, to unite around the Party central
leadership with Jiang Zemin at the core, and to reach a new level
of revolutionary military achievements, modernization and
standardization.
</P>
<P>
They are being asked to understand that the Party's third
generation of leaders with Jiang at the core are the faithful,
reliable, hard-working, and able inheritors of the cause of
building socialism with Chinese characteristics initiated by Deng
Xiaoping.
</P>
<P>
The circular called on the armed forces to more conscientiously
adhere to CPC leadership and be firmly in line with the Party
Central Committee ideologically, politically and in deed. 
</P>
