<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dunhuang Studies Seminar In East Chinese City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, September 21 (Xinhua) -- Scholars from Japan, the
Republic of Korea and all over China attended the '97 China
Seminar on Dunhuang Studies recently in Hangzhou, the capital of
Zhejiang province.
</P>
<P>
They discussed classification and systematization of documents,
and the history, geography, religion, folk customs, science,
technology, literature, and art of Dunhuang and presented 40
research papers.
</P>
<P>
More than 60,000 ancient books and a large number of historical
relics were discovered in 1900 in the Mogao Caves in Dunhuang
Grottoes in northwest China's Gansu province, and they have had a
tremendous impact on archeology everywhere, since then.
</P>
<P>
Many of the relics were removed from China before New China was
founded in 1949, leading some scholars to note that "Dunhuang
studies are in foreign countries". But China has made progress in
Dunhuang studies in recent years, according to Ji Xianlin, a
famous expert on Dunhuang, who shares this view.
</P>
<P>
The academics also discussed how to celebrate the 100th
anniversary of the discovery of the Mogao Caves in the year 2000.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970921.0080 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-21 12:14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Lebanon Raids Unlicensed Radio, TV Stations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, September 21 (Xinhua) -- A man was killed and three
others injuried today as Lebanese interior forces tried to shut
down unlicensed radio and television stations in north Lebanon, a
radio report said.
</P>
<P>
The forces last night blockaded the building in the northern
port city of Tripoli of al-Helail TV and Voice of Rights Radio
stations, both associated with the Islamic Unity Group (IUG).
</P>
<P>
This morning the forces raided the building and confiscated
audio-visual equipment after parliament members and ministers
failed to ease the tensions between the forces and IUG supporters
who gathered outside the building to protest.
</P>
<P>
The raid led to clashes in which one IUG member was shot dead
and three others wounded after they threw stones toward the forces.
</P>
<P>
According to a statement issued by the interior forces, some 74
IUG members were arrested, including the son of the group's
leader.
</P>
<P>
Since the government decided on the closure of unlicensed radio
and television stations in July this year, more than 30 such
stations had been shut down.
</P>
<P>
But a handful of stations in the country's eastern and
northern provinces continue to operate in defiance of the ban,
including a number of pro-Hezbollah radio stations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
