<DOCNO> XIE19970921.0082 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Technology Fair For East-West China Co-operation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LANZHOU, September 21 (Xinhua) -- A technology fair has been
held in Lanzhou, the capital of Gansu province, to boost
technological co-operation between businesses in the eastern and
northwestern parts of China.
</P>
<P>
Companies from the city of Shanghai and from 18 coastal
provinces did business in advanced technology with their
counterparts in landlocked western areas, where companies are not
very competitive because of a lack of technology.
</P>
<P>
A total of 287 agreements, involving 2.69 billion yuan (324
million US dollars), were signed at the three-day fair.
</P>
<P>
The technology traded at the fair has already proven useful in
production in the east, according tothe State Economic and Trade
Commission officials, who said that they expect better market
performance in backward enterprises. 
</P>
