<HEADLINE> Spouses of Finance Ministers, Bank Governors Honored </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 21 (Xinhua) -- Zhu Lin, wife of Chinese
Premier Li Peng, hosted a banquet in honor of the spouses of
finance ministers and central bank governors who are to attend the
September 23-25 annual meetings of the World Bank and the
International Monetary Fund (IMF), at noon today.
</P>
<P>
Zhu, accompanied by Betty Tung, wife of Tung Chee Hwa, chief
executive of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR) of
China, extended her welcome to the guests.
</P>
<P>
Some 100 distinguished women guests, including Mrs. Wolfensohn,
wife of President James David Wolfensohn of the World Bank, attend
the banquet.
</P>
<P>
Proposing a toast, Zhu said that the World Bank/IMF meetings
will help increase mutual understanding and friendship among the
women from all over the world.
</P>
<P>
Zhu also invited the guests to visit China's interior areas, so
as to learn more about the history of her country and acquaint
themselves with the achievements China had scored in its
modernization drive.
</P>
<P>
Premier Li Peng arrived here Saturday to address the opening of
the World Bank/IMF meetings on September 23 as head of government
of the host country.  
