<HEADLINE> MIGA Issues Record Guarantee Contracts in Fiscal 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Hong Kong, September 21 (Xinhua) -- The Multilateral Investment
Guarantee Agency (MIGA) said here today that it issued a record 70
guarantee contracts for 614 million U.S. dollars in new coverage
for projects in 25 developing countries in fiscal 1997 that ended
on June 30.
</P>
<P>
The 293 guarantee contracts issued by MIGA, a member of the
World Bank Group, have benefited 52 developing and transition
countries so far, MIGA said in its Annual Report available today.
</P>
<P>
Estimates of the developmental impact of the MIGA's fiscal 1997
projects include the creation of about 4,000 jobs and facilitation
of approximately 4.7 billion U.S. dollars in foreign direct
investments in the developing countries where they were located,
the document said.
</P>
<P>
Since its founding in April 1988, MIGA has facilitated an
estimated 20 billion U.S. dollars in foreign direct investments
and has helped to generate approximately 40,000 new jobs in the 52
host countries where the projects are located.
</P>
<P>
At a press conference here today, Akira Iida, executive
vice-president of MIGA, said that the Agency is optimistic about
chances of increasing operations in China, especially in China's
coastal provinces.
</P>
<P>
The objective of MIGA is to encourage the flow of investments
for productive purposes among member countries, in particular to
developing countries, by issuing guarantees against non-commercial
risks for foreign direct investments. 
</P>
</TEXT>
