<DOCNO> XIE19970921.0125 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> "El Nino" to Last Until March of 1998 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, September 20 (Xinhua) -- This year's "El Nino" climate
phenomenon with intense characteristics will last until March
of 1998, Peru's National Agrarian University (UNA) said today.
</P>
<P>
The university said that the "El Nino" 1997 phenomenon was not
detected on time because the anomaly in the temperature of the
Pacific Ocean waters off the Peruvian coast occurred first under
the surface at a depth between 80 and 250 meters.
</P>
<P>
No evident temperature increases were noticed at the surface
during the first few months of the year until May.
</P>
<P>
The sudden changes in the ocean temperature caused a variation
in the areas of distribution of most marine species.
</P>
<P>
The UNA considered that the phenomenon will acquire full
maturity and bring rains to South America in October and November.
</P>
<P>
El Nino appeared in the Equatorial Pacific, near South America,
because the winds, which normally blow from east to west, changed
direction, bringing warmer waters from the west to South American
coasts.
</P>
<P>
Previous experiences show that the water gets warmer below the
surface and later the warming extends upward to lesser depths.
</P>
<P>
A similar mechanism occurs during the phenomenon recession,
because deep waters cool first and some days later, because of new
upward movements, the cooling reaches shallower waters.
</P>
<P>
Because of the thermal inertia of the water, its temperature
does not change rapidly, so the anomaly in the temperature tend to
persist during several months. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970921.0126 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Maize Varieties to Boost Production </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, September 21 (Xinhua) -- Kenyan Agriculture Minister
Darius Mbela has released eight new maize varieties which will
bring the hope for farmers in arid and semi-arid areas of the
country to produce food for their needs.
</P>
<P>
The Sunday Standard today quoted the minister as saying Friday
that farmers from the dry parts of the country would have an
opportunity to produce maize to satisfy domestic needs.
</P>
<P>
The new Dryland Hybrid DH01 and DH02 is suitable for low
altitude, has better tolerance for drought and better
standability, and has 15 to 20 percent higher yield than ordinary
variety.
</P>
<P>
Pan 5195 variety suitable for medium altitude is
drought-tolerant and resistant to maize streak virus while Cagril
C 5222 variety suitable for medium altitude has good yields and
good standability with low ear placement.
</P>
<P>
The new maize varieties have been developed by four Kenyan
companies, that is, Kenya Seeds Company Ltd., Oil Crop
Development, Cargil and Pioneer.
</P>
<P>
The minister said that seed industry had been fully
liberalized by the government and any seed company, whether local
or foreign, was free to undertake seed research, breeding,
multiplication and marketing.
</P>
<P>
Following the liberalization of the seed industry, the Kenyan
government has set up Kenya Plant Health Inspectorate Service
which is in charge of all seed quality in the country two thirds
of which is arid and semi-arid land. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
