<HEADLINE> Seles Beats Sanchez Vicario For Princess Cup Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, September 21 (Xinhua) -- Monica Seles of the United
States scored her third title of the year winning over Arantxa
Sanchez Vicario of Spain in the final of the 450,000-U.S.-Dollar
Princess Cup tennis tournament here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The Yugoslav-born American, who ended her 11-month title
draught last month by taking back-to-back victories at Los Angeles
and Toronto, was taken to a tie break in the third set before
scoring a narrow 6-1, 3-6, 7-6 (7-5) victory.
</P>
<P>
Sanchez Vicario outplayed a game mixed with effective drop
shots and looping top spin, and, after being routed by Seles in
the first set, began to charge the net to pressure the top seed.
Sanchez Vicario forced Seles into a forehand error for a third
break and held for the set to level the contest.
</P>
<P>
In the decider, Seles had to recover after dropping the third
game to level at 3-3 after six deuces. She then missed a match
point at 30-40 in the 10th game, but made no mistake when the game
went to a tie-break.
</P>
<P>
With the victory, Seles collected a 14-1 record against Sanchez
Vicario, with the only defeat coming in the 1992 Canadian Open
final.
</P>
<P>
Seles received the winner's check of 79,000 U.S. dollars with
Sanchez Vicario taking 36,000 as runner-up. 
</P>
</TEXT>
