<HEADLINE> Changeover of Government in India's Uttar Pradesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 21 (Xinhua) -- Bharatiya Janata Party
(BJP) leader Kalyan Singh will take over as chief minister of
India's Uttar Pradesh today following the resignation of Chief
Minister Miss Mayawati on Saturday night, the local press said
today.
</P>
<P>
The smooth change of guard in India's most populous state was
the result of an unusual power-sharing arrangement between BJP and
Miss Mayawati's Bahujan Samaj Party (BSP).
</P>
<P>
With the emergence of a hung state assembly from the elections
held early this year, BJP and BSP have agreed to run a coalition
government in the state on a six month rotation.
</P>
<P>
On completion of a six-month term, Miss Mayawati submitted her
resignation to State Governor Romesh Bhandari on Saturday night,
requesting the governor to invite Singh for the formation of a new
state government.
</P>
<P>
Governor Bhandari asked Miss Mmayawati to continue as chief
minister till Kalyan Singh is sworn in along with his council of
ministers on Sunday afternoon in the Uttar Pradesh capital of
Lucknow.
</P>
<P>
The governor also made it clear that Kalyan Singh would not be
required to seek a vote of confidence in the state assembly.
</P>
</TEXT>
