<HEADLINE> Bank Role Urged in Sino-African Economic Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 21 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Li Peng and
President Omar Kabbaj of the African Development Bank today agreed
to strengthen the bank's role in developing Sino-African economic
cooperation and trade ties.
</P>
<P>
During their meeting here this morning, Li and Kabbaj noted
that China and African nations have maintained good cooperative
ties.
</P>
<P>
In the future, they said that China and Africa will continue to
develop economic and trade cooperation on the basis of equality,
mutual benefit and mutual complement and in conformity with
international practice.
</P>
<P>
The African Development Bank can play its role in the
development of Sino-African economic cooperation and trade ties,
they noted.
</P>
<P>
Kabbaj extended congratulations over the success of the
just-concluded 15th National Congress of the Communist Party of
China.
</P>
<P>
Li and Kabbaj are here to attend the forthcoming annual
meetings of the World Bank Group and the International Monetary
Fund, scheduled to open on September 23.  
</P>
</TEXT>
