<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Singapore Defense Minister Visits Britain &AMP; Sweden </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, September 21 (Xinhua) -- Singapore Deputy Prime
Minister and Defense Minister Tony Tan arrived in London today for
a week-long visit to Britain and Sweden, local newspapers reported
today.
</P>
<P>
During his stay in Britain, Tony Tan will call on British
Secretary for Defense George Robertson and meet senior defense
officials for discussions on defense ties and other matters, the
reports said.
</P>
<P>
He will also visit the permanent joint headquarters of the
British army, its aviation base and its submarine training
facility on the H.M.S. Dolphin.
</P>
<P>
From Wednesday to Saturday, Tony Tan will visit Sweden, where
he will call on Defense Minister Bjorn Von Sydow and meet
Secretary of State (Defense) Lena Jonsson to discuss bilateral
ties.
</P>
<P>
On Friday, he, accompanied by Mrs. Tan, will officiate at the
launch of the Republic of Singapore Navy's first submarine, the
RSS Challenger, at Malmo, Sweden.
</P>
<P>
The Minister, who oversees university education in Singapore,
will also visit the Defense Research Establishment and Stockholm
University, the reports said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
