<HEADLINE> Romania's Top Legislator Back From Russia Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, September 20 (Xinhua) -- Russia is opposed to
Romania's bid for NATO membership, Jan Diaconescu, chairman of the
Romanian Chamber of Deputies, said upon his return from Moscow
today.
</P>
<P>
Diaconescu paid a four-day visit in Russia as the head of a
parliamentary delegation.
</P>
<P>
He said he and Russian Foreign Minister Yevgeny Primakov had
discussed the issue of giving back the treasures belonging to
Romania by Russia. But the Russian side refused to negotiate, he
indicated.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that during World War I, the Romanian royal
family sent some treasures to the former Soviet Union for
preservation. So far these treasures have not been returned to
Romania.
</P>
<P>
A commentary carried by the Truth daily said the Romania-Russia
relations have not been on track since 1989. The two countries
have not signed any basic agreement and their economic ties are
far from satisfactory. 
</P>
</TEXT>
