<HEADLINE> Vice Premier Zhu Rongji Arrives in Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 21 (Xinhua) -- Vice Premier Zhu Rongji and
his wife Lao An arrived here from Beijing by air this morning.
</P>
<P>
Zhu, at the invitation of World Bank President James
Wolfensohn, made this trip to Hong Kong to deliver a keynote
speech at an international seminar scheduled for September 22 on
China's economic prospects in the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
The seminar is said to be the largest ever organized by the
World Bank on the subject of China.
</P>
<P>
Chief Executive of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region
(SAR) Tung Chee Hwa and his wife Betty Tung, Head and Deputy Head
of the Chinese government delegation to the WB/IMF annual meetings
on September 23-25 Liu Zhongli and Dai Xianglong, as well as
principal officials of the SAR greeted Zhu Rongji and his party at
the airport.
</P>
<P>
This is the first time for the World Bank and International
Monetary Fund (IMF) annual meetings to be held in China.
</P>
<P>
A series of international seminars are being held before the
meetings to discuss global economic conditions, and the whole day
of September 22 will be devoted to China.  
</P>
</TEXT>
