<HEADLINE> Albania Sends More Peacekeepers to Bosnia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, September 20 (Xinhua) -- The third contingent of
Albanian troops left by plane today to join the NATO-led
peacekeeping mission in Bosnia.
</P>
<P>
This contingent of 35 troops, headed by a lieutenant colonel,
will receive a one-month training in Germany before going to
Bosnia for a six-month mission, an Albanian TV report said.
</P>
<P>
This is seen as a move that will make closer the relations
between Albanian military forces and the armed forces of the North
Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO), the report said.
</P>
<P>
The last two contingents of Albanian peacekeepers were
dispatched to Bosnia in January 1996 and in February this year.
