<HEADLINE> Coca leaf Trade Down 18 Percent in Peru </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, September 20 (Xinhua) -- Coca leaf trade has dropped by
18 percent this year in Peru compared with last year, anti-drug
organization sources said.
</P>
<P>
The sources attributed the drop to the reduction of the area
cultivated to this plant.
</P>
<P>
Health Minister Marino Costa Bauer said that the area
cultivated with coca plants decreased by 18 percent during 1996,
from 115,000 hectares to 95,000 hectares.
</P>
<P>
He said that the coca leaf price has slipped from 40 U.S.
dollars per kilogram in 1993 to five dollars now. 
</P>
</TEXT>
