<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Private Businesses Enhances Anhui's Economic Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 21 (Xinhua) -- The private sector in east
China's Anhui Province drives economic development and had
contributed 11 percent of the province's industrial and commercial
taxes.
</P>
<P>
Today's Business Weekly of China Daily reported that the
province's 1.11 million family businesses and 17,600 private
enterprises have employed about 2.7 million people.
</P>
<P>
According to Wang Shengbang, director of the provincial
administration for industry and commerce, the private sector
accounts for 70 percent of his province's commercial, service and
catering outlets.
</P>
<P>
He said that the sector also helped promote reform of
state-owned enterprises in red by contracting, leasing or
purchasing small and medium sized state-owned or collective
enterprises and employing a lot of laid-off workers.
</P>
<P>
The increasing number of technicians, college graduates and
retired professionals has enhanced the private sector's
competitiveness.
</P>
<P>
The official said his province is home to 14 of the nation's
500 top private enterprises. 
</P>
</TEXT>
