<HEADLINE> Peschel Takes Time Trial Victory </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, September 20 (Xinhua) -- German Uwe Peschel won the
Grand Prix des Nations time trial on Saturday in Lac De Madine.
</P>
<P>
Briton Chris Boardman, world hour record holder and last year's
winner in the 72-kilometer time trial around Lake Madine in
eastern France, was third behind Belgian Marc Streel.
</P>
<P>
Peschel won a bronze medal in the 1995 World Championships in
Colombia behind Spaniards Miguel Indurain and Abraham Olano.
</P>
<P>
The German struggled to find a team at the start of the season,
finally ending up with the modest Slovenian-based Italian outfit
Cantina Tollo. Then he resigned from Cantino Tollo in Augugst and
now rides for the semi-professional German team Schauff. 
</P>
