<DOCNO> XIE19970921.0225 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hefei Foreign-Funded Ventures </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, September 21 (Xinhua) -- Fifty leading foreign firms in
Hefei, capital city of east China's Anhui Province, generated a
combined output of 2.35 billion yuan (283 million US dollars) in
the first half of this year, up 57.3 percent on last year's same
period.
</P>
<P>
Local government statistics show that said enterprises recorded
pretax profits of 140 million yuan (16.87 million US dollars), up
71.8 percent on the 1996 figure.
</P>
<P>
Hefei, home to 1,140 foreign-funded firms, has used 4.1 billion
US dollars of foreign investment, with total contracted
investments by the end of June standing at 1.5 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Some 65 percent of approved foreign-funded firms have entered
operations this year.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the number of loss-making enterprises in the city
has dropped by 12.4 percent, with the combined profits of the said
businesses rising by 40 percent to 43.73 million yuan (5.27
million US dollars) in the first six months of this year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
