<HEADLINE> More Investment in Copper Mining in Chile </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, September 20 (Xinhua) -- Chilean and foreign mining
firms will invest about 4.8 billion U.S. dollars in the next three
years in the sector, the Chilean Copper Commission (Cochilco) said.
</P>
<P>
Three billion dollars out of the total will be used for the
Dona Ines de Collahuasi and Los Pelambres copper projects, said
Cochilco.
</P>
<P>
Three other new copper mining projects in San Antonio, Lomas
Bayas and Tesoro-Leonor will need more than 1.5 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
The Chilean commission said that an investment of 1.5 billion
dollars is expected in the mining sector this year, a figure that
surpasses by almost 70 percent the amount invested last year.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
