<HEADLINE> Qian Qichen Arrives in New York to Attend U.N. Assembly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, September 20 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier
and Foreign Minister Qian Qichen arrived here this evening to
attend the 52nd session of the U.N. General Assembly.
</P>
<P>
Qian, heading a Chinese delegation, will give a speech on
current international situation as well as China's domestic
development during the general debate of the Assembly, which is
scheduled to begin on Monday, a spokesman for the Chinese Mission
to the U.N. said.
</P>
