Qian is also expected to meet with leaders of some other states
attending the session, spokesman Chen Ranfeng said.
</P>
<P>
The 52nd session of the U.N. General Assembly, opened last
Tuesday, is expected to last until mid-December with its focus on
the reform of the world body. 
