<HEADLINE> France Wins Doubles in Davis Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, September 20 (Xinhua) -- Fabrice Santoro and
Guillaume Raoux became the heros of the defending champion
France, as they won the doubles on Saturday in Ghent, Belgium to
avoid the relegation of the team from the World Group.
</P>
<P>
The French combination defeated Belgium's Filip Dewulf and
Libor Pimek 5-7, 7-5, 7-5, 6-1.
</P>
<P>
The victory left Belgium leading the best-of-five tie 2-1
heading into Sunday's reverse singles.
</P>
<P>
France, which beat Sweden in last year's final, came to
neighboring Belgium without its No. 2 player Arnauld Boetsch and
further lost Wimbledon finalist Cedric Pioline with a back injury
during his opening match Friday.
</P>
<P>
On Sunday, Dewulf will play either Raoux or Lionel Roux. And if
France continues its comeback, Santoro will face Johan Van Herck
in the deciding singles. 
</P>
</TEXT>
