<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 20 (Xinhua) -- Kazakhstan and Uzbekistan
played a 1-1 draw Saturday at Almaty's Central Stadium in an Asian
Group B World Cup qualifying game in Almaty, Kazakhstan.
</P>
<P>
The first goal was scored by Kazakstan's Ruslan Batiyev on a
penalty kick in the 84th minute, which was given after the Uzbek
goalkeeper Pavel Bugalo fouled forward Oleg Litvinenko in front of
the goal.
</P>
<P>
Two minutes later, Uzbekistan's Oleg Shatskih pulled back and
then later received a yellow card for arguing with the referee,
who initially did not seem to count the goal. 
