<HEADLINE> Woodies Keep Aussies Alive in Davis Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 20 (Xinhua) -- Mark Woodforde and Todd
Woodbridge kept Australia alive in the Davis Cup semifinals
against the United States, beating Pete Sampras and Todd Martin
3-6, 7-6 (7-5), 6-2, 6-4 here on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Woodforde and Woodbridge used superior teamwork to defeat two
players more fancied in the singles play. Sampras and Martin,
although 6-1 lifetime as a pair going into the match, were playing
together for the first time since 1995.
</P>
<P>
The United States, which won both singles matches Friday, will
take a 2-1 lead into Sunday's reverse singles of the best-of-five
series. Sampras will play U.S. Open champion Patrick Rafter, while
Michael Chang will face Mark Philippoussis at the FitzGerald Tennis
Center.
</P>
<P>
The winner will face Italy or Sweden in the finals slated for
November 28-30. Sweden leads Italy 2-1 after splitting Friday's
singles and capturing today's doubles. 
</P>
