<HEADLINE> Germany Takes Unbeatable 3-0 Lead </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, September 20 (Xinhua) -- Germany took an unbeatable 3-0
lead over Mexico after winning Saturday's doubles make sure of
retaining its berth in the World Group of the Davis Cup in Essen,
Germany.
</P>
<P>
The doubles victory assured Germany of victory in the
best-of-five series that concludes Sunday with the reverse singles.
</P>
<P>
Marc-Kevin Goellner and Jens Knippschild clinched the tie for
Germany by beating Oscar Ortiz and David Roditi 7-5 (7-4), 7-6
(7-4), 4-6, 6-3.
</P>
<P>
The Germans used two hours 28 minutes to outplay the
hard-fighting Mexican duo.
</P>
<P>
The Germans won the Davis Cup title three times between 1988
and 1983, led by Boris Becker.
</P>
<P>
Becker, who has announced his retirement from Grand Slam
tennis, returned to the team Friday and won the opening singles
against Luis Herrera 7-5, 6-2, 6-3 and his teammate Goellner beat
Alejandro Hernandez 7-5, 6-3, 6-3. 
</P>
