<HEADLINE> Nigeria Reveals Plan for Sydney Paralympics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, September 20 (Xinhua) -- The Nigeria Sports Association
for the Disabled said here today it will begin preparations for
the Sydney Paralympics 2000 early next year.
</P>
<P>
The athletes for the first phase of the preparations would be
selected at the 2nd WINCO Foam National Games for the Disabled,
which opened here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
According to Cosmas Okoli, chairman of the association, the
selected athletes would take part in many international
championships and also undertake training tours to improve their
skills before the Sydney games.
</P>
<P>
The decision for early preparations was borne out of the fact
that the association was no longer contended with just winning
medals at the paralympics but being among the leaders on the
medal's table, Okoli said. 
</P>
