<HEADLINE> China Wins Three Titles at World Sports Acrobatics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANCHESTER, September 20 (Xinhua) -- China's defending world
champions Song Min/Li Renjie successfully collected another two
individual gold medals after defeating their strong opponents at
the World Sports Acrobatics Championships in Manchester on
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Although the Chinese duo were ranked as favorites to win all
the three titles of the men's pairs event, today's balance final
put the Chinese players under extreme pressure when a British
combination won the highest 10-point. The experienced Chinese
players, with previous round advantage, finally won the title by a
small margin.
</P>
<P>
The men's pairs tempo final almost put all the audience in the
Mancheters National Cycling Center on their feet when a pair of
Russian players in high-powered fighting form seemed one step away
from toppling the defending Champions. With the Russian and
Chinese players getting exactly the same score, the national flags
of two sports acrobatics superpowers simutaneously flew at the
highest level.
</P>
<P>
At the women's pairs balance final, Chinese combination Liao
Xinxin and Lao Peiling put up an fantastic performance, putting
the third gold medal into the Chinese delegation's gold
wardrobe. Chinese tumbler Chen Bo got a silver medal at the men's
tumbling twisting final.
</P>
<P>
In addition, Chinese players also pocketed four bronze medals
in final clashes of the men's groups balance/tempo, women's mixed
pairs tempo and women's groups balance events.
</P>
<P>
The powerful Russian troops altogether won eight titles in a
series of finals, with another powerhouse Ukraine collecting two
gold medals. Belarus and Britain got one gold medal each.
</P>
<P>
In the all-around competions to be held tomorrow, China's Song
Min/Li Renjie and Lao Peiling/Liao Xinxin are also expected to win
another two gold medals for China. The final curtain of the
four-day championships will fall tomorrow afternoon. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
