<HEADLINE> Switzerland Beats South Korea in Davis Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, September 20 (Xinhua) -- Marc Rosset and Lorenzo Manta
recorded a doubles victory over South Korea on Saturday in
Locarno, Switzerland to give Switzerland an unbeatable 3-0 lead in
the Davis Cup world group qualifying tie.
</P>
<P>
The victory secured Switzerland a place in the 16-team world
group for the fourth consecutive year.
</P>
<P>
Although forced to tie-breaks in the first two sets, Rosset and
Manta finally bested South Korea's Yoon Yong-Il and Kim Dong-Huyn
7-6 (7-5), 7-6 (7-5), 6-4.
</P>
<P>
The Swiss pair suffered a scare in the first set, with the South
Koreans taking them to two break points on Manta's serve.
</P>
<P>
The Swiss did not drop a single set in all the three matches
against the South Koreans.
</P>
<P>
Switzerland and South Korea will play dead rubber reverse
singles on Sunday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
